Clarence Thomas was confirmed a Supreme Court justice on 16 October
1991.

Thomas was born in 1948.  He attended catholic schools and finished
Yale Law in 1974.  He then changed from a liberal to a conservative
outlook.

Thomas held positions as a lawyer and a judge.  He was helped by
affirmative action.</SUM>
